## The name

Apache-2.0 grants no rights to the project name (its §6). "Agentic Software Operations" — the name and any
associated identity — is **not** part of the license grant. Fork and build on the code
freely, but please don't release a fork, product, or company *as* "Agentic Software Operations." Saying your
tool is *based on* or *a fork of* Agentic Software Operations is fine. See [`NOTICE`](NOTICE).

"Atlassian", "Jira", and "Confluence" are trademarks of Atlassian Pty Ltd. Agentic Software Operations is an
independent project, not affiliated with or endorsed by Atlassian; those marks are used
only to describe what the tool works with.

